<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H2">Dropdown Component</Heading>

<Paragraph>
    Dropdowns are menus that display a list of links and other elements. Dropdowns can be toggled.
</Paragraph>

<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H3">Documentation</Heading>
<Paragraph IsStretchedLinkContainer="true">
    The documentation for the <code>Dropdown</code> component is avaible on the <Anchor Url="https://github.com/MikaBerglund/Blazor-Bootstrap/wiki/Dropdown" IsStretched="true" OpenInNewTab="true">Blazor Bootstrap Wiki</Anchor>
</Paragraph>


<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H3" MarginTop="Spacing.Five">Examples</Heading>
<Paragraph>
    The two examples below shows the variations you can have with the <code>Dropdown</code> component.
</Paragraph>

<Dropdown>
    <DropdownToggleLink Text="Text toggle" />
    <DropdownMenu>
        <DropdownItem Text="Active" IsActive="true" />
        <DropdownItem Text="Disabled" IsDisabled="true" />
        <DropdownDivider />
        <DropdownItem Text="Normal" />
    </DropdownMenu>
</Dropdown>


<Dropdown MarginTop="Spacing.Two">
    <DropdownToggleButton Color="NamedColor.Primary" OnClick="(e) => { }">Button toggle</DropdownToggleButton>
    <DropdownMenu>
        <DropdownItem Text="Active" IsActive="true" />
        <DropdownItem Text="Disabled" IsDisabled="true" />
        <DropdownDivider />
        <DropdownItem Text="Normal" />
    </DropdownMenu>
</Dropdown>